Package com.cg.training.models

Class AdminTest

java.lang.Object
com.cg.training.models.AdminTest
public class AdminTest extends Object
This class contains tests for the Admin functionality. It checks how the Admin interacts with the list of doctors, and ensures that everything works as expected. It also tests the availability and profile of doctors.
Author:
Sampritee Dey

  • Method Details

    • setUp

      public void setUp()
      This method runs before each test. It sets up the Admin object and a list of doctors. It prepares the data so each test can run with a fresh set of objects.

    • testRemoveDoctor_ValidId

      public void testRemoveDoctor_ValidId()
      Test case for removing a doctor from the list by their ID. This test checks if the doctor is successfully removed when given a valid ID.

    • testRemoveDoctor_InvalidId

      public void testRemoveDoctor_InvalidId()
      Test case for removing a doctor from the list with an invalid ID. This test checks that nothing happens if the ID is not found.

    • testShowProfile

      public void testShowProfile()
      Test case for showing the profile of the Admin. This test checks if the Admin's details (ID and name) are printed correctly.

    • testDoctorAvailability

      public void testDoctorAvailability()
      Test case for checking the availability of a doctor. This test checks if a doctor is available and if we can change their availability.

    • testDoctorShowProfile

      public void testDoctorShowProfile()
      Test case for showing the profile of a doctor. This test checks if the doctor's details (ID, name, and availability) are printed correctly.

    • testDoctorListIntegrity

      public void testDoctorListIntegrity()
      Test case to check the integrity of the list of doctors. This test ensures the list of doctors contains the correct IDs and names.

    • testAdminGetters

      public void testAdminGetters()
      Test case to check the Admin's getters for ID and name. This test ensures that the Admin's ID and name are correct.

    • testRemoveDoctor_EmptyList

      public void testRemoveDoctor_EmptyList()
      Edge case test to remove a doctor when the list is empty. This test ensures that nothing breaks if you try to remove a doctor from an empty list.

    • testRemoveDoctor_NullId

      public void testRemoveDoctor_NullId()
      Edge case test to remove a doctor with a null ID. This test ensures that nothing breaks if you try to remove a doctor with a null ID.
